@flint v0 hybrid
@cb[
  μ1=auth_mw;
  κ1=preserve_single_err_map;
  κ2=no_widen_skew;
  σ=30000;
  τ1=refresh_loop
]

G: fix(μ1.expiry_cmp)
C: κ1 ∧ κ2
H: "expMs < nowMs" ∧ skew_not_encoded ⇒ boundary(nowMs==expMs+σ) ⇒ τ1
P: normalize(expMs,ms) → Δ("nowMs > expMs + σ") → single_site(μ1) → next(err) unchanged
V: unit(expMs==nowMs)==pass ∧ unit(nowMs==expMs+σ)==pass ∧ unit(nowMs==expMs+σ+1)==401 ∧ unit(missing_token)==401 ∧ unit(malformed)==401 ∧ unit(sec_vs_ms_mismatch)==401
R: ! widen_beyond_σ ∧ ! multi_site_drift ∧ ! refresh_path_disagree
Q: refresh_issuer_uses_same_σ ?
A: patch=cmp→"nowMs > expMs + 30000" ∧ reg_test=boundary(+0,+σ,+σ+1)

[AUDIT]
bug: strict "<" plus no skew encoding flips at exact boundary, reject vs refresh disagree, loop.
fix: one site in auth_mw, compare nowMs > exp

@flint v0 hybrid
@cb[
  μ1=loadUser;
  κ1=order_preserve;
  κ2=single_err_map;
  τ1=next_err;
  σ1=async_await
]

G: refactor(μ1, σ1) ∧ minimal_diff
C: κ1 ∧ κ2 ∧ preserve(τ1)
P: validate(missing_id) → await(db.findUser) → branch(not_found) → audit.log → cache.set → res
H: try_catch ⇒ τ1 ∧ single_site
V: test(missing_id_400) ∧ test(not_found_404) ∧ test(db_err→next_err) ∧ test(happy_path_audit∧cache) ∧ test(no_double_callback)
R: ! this_binding(db.findUser) ∧ ! promisify_semantics ∧ ! duplicate_next_call
Q: db.findUser_returns_promise ?
A: async μ1; guard(!req.id)→next_err(400); try{user=await db.findUser(id)}catch(e){return next(e)}; if(!user)return next_err(404); await audit.log(...); await cache.set(...); res.json(user)

[AUDIT]
make loadUser async. keep order: id check, db lookup, not-found branch, audit, cache, respond. wrap db.findUser in try/catch, route all failures through next(err) at one site. verify db.findUser returns promise or wrap with promisify, watch this-binding. tests cover missing id, not found, db error mapping,
